      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Insufficient or defective intrinsic factor can disrupt B12 absorption, leading to a deficiency. When B12 is not absorbed correctly, it can accumulate in tissues such as the nervous system, red blood cells, and kidneys. This can cause a range of symptoms, including neurological problems like numbness and tingling in the hands and feet, fatigue, weakness, and impairments in cognitive function. In severe cases, it can also lead to megaloblastic anemia, with abnormally large red blood cells that are prone to breaking down.",
